name: Nike Mag Raffle Tickets
description:
Her is your Chance to win one of the most sought after shoes on the planet. Here is a some history of these Rare Kicks: Raffle tickets are $25 each buy as many as you like for  a better chance to win. 
      There were only 1500 pairs of the Nike Mag were auctioned off for charity via eBay. 150 pairs were auctioned off a day for 10 days
Auctions started at 8:30PM PST and ends on September 18 2011 Auctions will be hosted at eBay’s Fashion Vault Proceeds benefit the Michael J. Fox Foundation. Official title is the 2011 Nike Mag. 

I was fortunate enough to win my pair size 10 on the last day of the auctions. I have had these shoes stored in the original box since the day I got them!  
The Raffle for these shoes will take place at Retro & Vintage inside Eastland mall. There will only be limted amount of tickets available. you can purchase as many tickets as you like. Once tickets are sold out I will have the drawing the next day. I will announce the time of the drawing via Video on InstaGram, Facebook & Twitter. I also welcome anyone who Participated to come up to Retro & Vintage for the live drawing.

Good luck for all those who Participate!

These Finishes have NOT been tested for use on bare skin or hair.
Disclaimer: Images are for visual representation, Please test a small area before committing to use our products. JrAddicts Glow Ployurethane Finish  will not be held responsible for any misuse or damage caused. Paints are not suitable for children unless supervised or specifically tested for child safety and usage.

name: Jordan 1 Dorenbecher (DB) 1.4
description:
This is for the custom work only. 
You will need have a pair of St. Patrick Day Jordan 1 Retro from March of 2013. Any other color way will require more work and cost more to be customized into this custom. Not saying that it cant be done on other colorways it just requires more work, Which will cost more to do. Please contact first if you are sending another colorway, so I can give you pricing.

Instructions:
(a) contact me to send your shoes in.

(b) Ill send you the address where you can send to.

(c) Make Payment thru PayPal for your Custom work

(d) Send the shoes via shipping company of your choice

(e) Once shoes are received they will be completed in the order in which they are received. 

(f) Shoes will be shipped back to the customer

 Custom Disclaimer:
 I guarantee all my custom work are 100% professionally done. Normal wear on any customs will not have any of the following flaws:
No peeling
No fading
No cracking 
No rubbing off
The paint/dye I use is Angelus Which is waterproof and a trusted paint among Shoe Artist every where. 

Most of All I offer a way for you the Customer to be among the elite to have something different that's not seen everyday. The Sneaker Community is growing larger everyday. Finding something different or rare is getting EXTREMELY DIFFICULT!!! That's the service I'm providing for you!!! Your Custom Shoes will be the "Neck Breaker"! The Talk of your school. Your Friends "Envy". Like Tattoos Custom shoes are and will become addictive. 
If you do not like Attention or Don't waste your time!!!! If you Love being the talk of all who see whats on your feet you have to go with a pair of customs! Its worth the price. Believe me!
